*

* Represents the bounds and link on a page of the PDF document. Weblinks are those links implicitly * embedded in PDF pages. * Note: Only weblinks that are embedded will be supported. Links encoded as * plain text will be returned as part of {@link PdfPageTextContent}.

methods.name: public List<RectF> getBounds()
methods.comment:
*

* Gets the bounds of the embedded weblink represented as a list of {@link RectF}. Links which * are spread across multiple lines will be surrounded by multiple {@link RectF} in order of * viewing. *

Note: Each {@link RectF} represents a bound of the weblink in a single * line and defines the coordinates of its 4 edges (left, top, right and bottom) in * points (1/72"). The developer will need to render the highlighter as well as intercept the * touch events for functionalities such as clicking the link. * * @return The bounds of the link.

methods.name: public Uri getUri()
methods.comment:
*

* Gets the weblink on the page of the PDF document. Weblinks are those links implicitly * embedded in PDF pages. * Note: Only weblinks that are embedded will be supported. Links encoded as * plain text will be returned as part of {@link PdfPageTextContent}. * * @return The weblink embedded on the page.
